For the past 10 days I’ve been waiting for God to give me a word for the year… I would typically open my bible and something would resonate and stick out to me. This year I had to be a little bit more patient, but it came. ☺️ As I bent down to plug something in I saw a stack of books that haven’t been picked up for a long while. They are basically on “display” on an office shelf. The bottom book is What On Earth Am I Here For by Rick Warren. I felt God telling me to pick it up and open it to Day 10 (today is the 10th), and there it was…..

SURRENDER 

A word that the world would consider unpopular, and almost always used in a negative context. We would rather talk about winning, succeeding, overcoming, and conquering than yielding, submitting, obeying and surrendering…. Yet it is a word Paul uses in Romans to urge us to do. To fully surrender to self and worship God. The heart of worship is surrender.

As I went on reading the chapter I learned there are 3 barriers that block surrender.

1. Fear
2. Pride
3. Confusion

It means to let go of control (hello Britney 😅) and instead of trying harder we trust more. We let go and let God work. I don’t know about you but I’m all for letting go of fear, pride and confusion. 

Of course it’s great to have personal goals and things we want to achieve, but when we make it our goal to please Him first I believe everything else will fall into place.

I’m praying God will help me to remember this word daily, as I know it won’t come easy…. And to acknowledge that nothing under His control can ever be out of control.

Have you picked a word for 2024? If so I’d love to hear it and read them to my kids. Karson is still working on his, but Prestyn has chosen Faith, Scotlynn has chosen Gratitude and Dawson has chosen Brave. (Conveniently those are Prestyn and Dawson’s middle names 😆)
